overview: In April 1978, the annual Ensenada Yacht Race from Newport Beach, California, to Ensenada, Mexico, occurred over the course of twenty-four hours. More than 600 yachts and sailboats competed in the 200-mile race. In the final stretch into Ensenada Harbor, the winds calmed, leaving the boats moving slowly to the finish line.
tagline: Every year, thousands of men leave the earth behind. They launch themselves into another world of beauty, excitement, and danger. The world of the sea. Join them!
title: Pacific High
